 World Spawn - the world map is selected and confirmed automatically based on the world spawn point that the game client is aware of. Can break if the server is using the vanilla compass item for a custom function. 
 
 Single - each dimension has a single world map that is automatically confirmed. Useful for simple servers with a single world. 
 
 Server - install the world map mod on the server side to use this automatic mode.

gui.xaero_box_waypoints_clamp_depth.description:
The screen depth at which in-game waypoints stop getting smaller when you go further away from them. 
 Use this if you want to make waypoints that are far away bigger/smaller on the screen. Use the "Waypoint In-Game Scale" setting to also affect the size of waypoints when you are close to them. 
 
 For the "Auto" option, go all the way to the left. 
 The automatic option attempts to give you the best value for the default values of scale types, taking your FOV and screen height into account. 
 
 Default values in older mod versions: 
 Clamp Depth: 12 
 In-Game Scale: 2.5 
 Name Text Scale: 0.5 
 Distance Text Scale: 0.8

gui.xaero_wm_box_detect_ambiguous_y.description: A single pixel on the map can contain multiple transparent layers and an opaque block under them. In older non-cache map data files, only the Y level (height) of the opaque block is stored in such cases, which often makes it unsafe to blindly teleport to the stored Y coordinate. When this setting is ON, the mod treats such map pixels as it would undiscovered chunks. It defaults to 2D waypoints and disables direct teleportation to such pixels. Disable this at your own risk!

config.entity_texture_features.emissive_.description:
This sets whether emissives use 'Brighter' or 'Default' rendering
This is hard to describe, just try it out in-game :)
Bright rendering makes the emissive appear at max brightness if need be
and is only partially compatible with shaders, etc.
Default rendering respects the default renderers effects on entities,
the direction of each surface will have slight brightness variation
and the emissives will be a bit less bright overall
as well as usually smaller bloom with shaders.
Compatible mode, automatically adjusts the rendering mode for best shader compatibility & brightness
Block entities will always be on default mode unless Iris is installed.

craftpresence.command.usage.main.description:
§lCraftPresence - Sub-Commands:
 §rSyntax: §6/<cp|craftpresence> <command>

 §6§lreboot §r- Reboot RPC
 §6§lshutdown §r- Shut down RPC
 §6§lcompile §r- Test the output of a placeholder expression, via Starscript
 §6§lsearch §r- Search for valid placeholders available to use with Rich Presence
 §6§lreload §r- Reloads CraftPresence data based on settings
 §6§lrequest §r- View join request info
 §6§lexport §r- View export commands for mod data
 §6§lview §r- View a variety of display data
 §6§lhelp §r- Views this page

block.rsgauges.glass_day_timer.help.description:
A small glass device that emits a
 redstone signal from a configured
 start (day) time to a configured
 end time. The time span is set
 with buttons on the device front
 face (24 hour format, where 06:00
 is sunrise). These buttons also
 allow to set output power and a
 randomizing value. Latter means
 delaying to switch on or off for
 a random time span, where higher
 values cause longer delays. Output is
 to the block where the sensor is
 placed on. Does not emit switching
 sounds.
${rsgauges.switch.feature.outputconfig.help}

block.rsgauges.industrial_light_sensor.h.description:
A small device that measures the
 local light level at its location
 and emits a redstone signal
 depending on on-threshold and
 off-threshold set with small
 buttons on the front face.§r These
 buttons also allow to set output
 power and debouncing. Debouncing
 delays switching off or on until
 the light level is stable, higher
 values means better noise
 filtering, but also more switching
 delay. If on and off settings are
 identical, then the measured
 light level must exactly match
 the set value. Output is to the
 block where the sensor is placed on.
${rsgauges.switch.feature.outputconfig.help}
${rsgauges.switch.feature.linksource.help}

config.supplementaries.wind_vane.power_s.description:
Wind vane animation swings according to this equation: 
angle(time) = max_angle_1*sin(2pi*time*pow/period_1) + <max_angle_2>*sin(2pi*time*pow/<period_2>)
where:
 - pow = max(1,redstone_power*<power_scaling>)
 - time = time in ticks
 - redstone_power = block redstone power
<power_scaling> = how much frequency changes depending on power. 2 means it spins twice as fast each power level (2* for rain, 4* for thunder)
increase to have more distinct indication when weather changes

block.rsgauges.industrial_switchlink_rel.description:
A small industrial switching
 device that is optimized to be
 used as a Switch Link relay with
 redstone input. The relay cannot
 emit redstone signals, instead
 it allows Link Pearls inside to
 trigger when the redstone power
 of the block it is mounted on
 changes. By double-left clicking
 empty handed you can change the
 input polarity (inverted means
 active-low) and strength
 sensitivity (default weak, strong
 means that strong power is needed
 to trigger the links). Muffled,
 therefore very silent. Can also
 be manually activated like a
 lever for testing.
${rsgauges.switch.feature.linktarget.help}
${rsgauges.switch.feature.linksource.help}

gui.xaero_box_category_list_add.description:
Supports entity identifiers or patterns with special characters * ) ( and |. 
 
 * - matches anything. 
 )( - parenthesis, mostly for usage with |. 
 | - the OR operator to match different sequences in the same location. 
 
 For example: 
 minecraft:creeper 
 minecraft:zombie(_villager|_horse) - zombie villagers and horses. 
 minecraft:a*l - any vanilla entity which starts with 'a' and ends with 'l'.

fpsreducer.config.tooltip.profile.coolin.description:
§eProfile: §oSituational Cooling (High)§r
More powerful load suppression depending on the situation. (For weak PC.) In addition to the behavior of Eco profile, FPS will be limited to 30fps when the character is stationary, in inventory screen or in any GUI screen.

§eProfile: §oSituational Cooling (Low)§r
Proactively control the load depending on the situation. (For PC that runs at 60fps or higher.) In addition to the behavior of Eco profile, FPS will be limited to 60fps when the character is stationary, in inventory screen or in any GUI screen. Depending on VSync and Max Framerate settings in the Video Settings, the effect will be less effective.

block.rsgauges.glass_entity_detector.hel.description:
A small glass device that
 observes a defined volume and
 emits a redstone signal if it
 sees an entity. The volume is two
 blocks above and below, and 'range'
 in front, left and right (covers
 180 degrees). The range can be
 configured with small buttons on
 the front face, together with the
 output strength, the number of
 entities seen, and the entity type

gui.xaero_box_pushbox_potion_effects.description:
An invisible box around the vanilla potion effects display that pushes the mod's interfaces out of the way. 
 
 Normal type's collision box is equal to its size and only pushes interfaces by the necessary distance. 
 
 Screen Height type's collision box is stretched across the whole screen height and always shifts colliding interfaces vertically by the Normal type's height. This can be very useful when you have multiple interfaces in a column and want all of them to be pushed.

block.rsgauges.industrial_day_timer.help.description:
A small device that emits a
 redstone signal from a configured
 start (day) time to a configured
 end time. The time span is set
 with buttons on the device front
 face (24 hour format, where 06:00
 is sunrise). These buttons also
 allow to set output power and a
 randomizing value. Latter means
 delaying to switch on or off for
 a random time span, where higher
 values cause longer delays. Output
 is to the block where the sensor
 is placed on.
